Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` to hook platform-native callbacks directly:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity loses focus (Android OnPause)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity is no longer visible (Android OnStop)
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // Runs when the app enters background (iOS DidEnterBackground)
        }));
#endif
});
```

### Cross-platform alternative

If you don't need the native parameters, the **`Window.Stopped`** event maps to all three (`OnStop`, `DidEnterBackground`, `VisibilityChanged(false)`). Override `CreateWindow` in `App.cs`:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* app backgrounded on all platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```

### Key gotchas

- **Keep handlers fast** — Android enforces ~5s ANR; iOS has limited background time.
- **Android back button** can skip `Stopped` and go straight to `Destroying`, so save critical state in both.
- **`Deactivated` ≠ `Stopped`** — pulling down the notification shade fires `Deactivated`/`OnPause` but not `Stopped`.
